Four ORTEC semiconductor detectors of depletion
depth near 500 mu-m were mounted on the periphery of
the wheel. The active area of the detectors (about
50 mm2) was reduced to 4.5 mm2 by collimators. The
angular spread of the detector at the target was 0.47
degr. and the solid angle for detection near 2*10**(-4)
sr. The detector resolution was estimated, using 241Am
alphas, to be 24 keV.

The stability of the current integrator was within 3%
down to a minimum current of 0.1 mu-A, as estimated
from repeat runs on the same target at the same energy.
Targets were made by evaporating natural vanadium metal
on to self supporting carbon films of about 10 to 20
mu-g/cm2. The thickness of the vanadium target was
5 mu-g/cm2.
